title: Zeisberger's NHL power rankings
text:
MIKE ZEISBERGER'S WEEKLY NHL POWER RANKINGS 
(Last week's rankings in parentheses. Saturday's games not included) 
1. Montreal Canadiens (1) Price off to another Hart-like start. 
2. Washington Capitals (12) Oshie, Williams fitting in nicely. 
3. Dallas Stars (4) Niemi providing much-needed stability. 
4. Nashville Predators (3) Arguably the deepest blueline in the league. 
5. Tampa Bay Lightning (9) Stamkos off to good start. 
6. New York Rangers (16) Nash struggling early on. 
7. New York Islanders (11) Glad to have Halak playing again. 
8. St. Louis Blues (5) Injuries to Stastny, Schwartz a concern. 
9. Minnesota Wild (6) Dubnyk picking up where he left off. 
10. Chicago Blackhawks (17) Losing Keith for at least a month really hurts. 
11. Los Angeles Kings (23) Four consecutive victories. 
12. San Jose Sharks (2) Couture injury stings. 
13. Winnipeg Jets (8) Wheeler hot out of the gates. 
14. Ottawa Senators (14) Hamburglar healthy again. 
15. Vancouver Canucks (13) Sedins continue to defy Father Time. 
16. Pittsburgh Penguins (20) Crosby, Kessel split up. 
17. Detroit Red Wings (7) Growing pains for Blashill after hot start. 
18. Florida Panthers (10) Need to find consistency. 
19. Philadelphia Flyers (18) Running hot and cold. 
20. Boston Bruins (26) More speed, more youth required. 
21. Anaheim Ducks (25) Is Boudreau's job in jeopardy? 
22. Arizona Coyotes (15) Mike Smith having rebound season. 
23. Colorado Avalanche (19) Poor possession numbers. 
24. Edmonton Oilers (28) Poor defensive play continues. 
25. Calgary Flames (22) Dougie Hamilton struggling. 
26. Buffalo Sabres (21) Shredded by Habs Friday. 
27. Carolina Hurricanes (27) Struggling to score goals. 
28. Toronto Maple Leafs (24) Bozak on IR. 
29. New Jersey Devils (29) Just not a lot of talent here. 
30. Columbus Blue Jackets (30) Torts says Johansen out of shape. Sponsored Links
